WEBVTT

00:03.254 --> 00:04.545
[ GLASS RATTLES ]

00:07.007 --> 00:09.470
[ GLASS RATTLES ]

00:09.470 --> 00:12.183
[ ELLIPHANT'S "NEVER BEEN
IN LOVE" PLAYING ]

00:14.515 --> 00:17.848
♪ SUMMER'S COLD
AND I AM BROKE, MAN ♪

00:17.848 --> 00:21.062
♪ AND MY BILLS DON'T WAIT ♪

00:21.062 --> 00:23.814
♪ MOMMY'S ANGRY,
CLUB IS OLD ♪

00:23.814 --> 00:27.818
♪ AND I'M BORN TOO LATE ♪

00:27.818 --> 00:31.072
♪ VICIOUS CITY
TRY TO BREAK ME ♪

00:31.072 --> 00:34.325
♪ BUT I WALK RIGHT THROUGH ♪

00:34.325 --> 00:37.868
♪ I COULDN'T CARE LESS
NOR AM I FEARLESS ♪

00:37.868 --> 00:39.210
♪ ON MY WAY TO YOU ♪

00:39.210 --> 00:40.501
Meredith:
THEY FOUND THIS GUY IN MAINE

00:40.501 --> 00:43.214
WHO HAD BEEN LIVING
COMPLETELY ALONE IN THE WOODS

00:43.214 --> 00:44.505
FOR 30 YEARS.

00:44.505 --> 00:46.877
♪ I DON'T CARE,
NO, I DON'T CARE ♪

00:46.877 --> 00:49.130
THEY CALLED HIM
THE LAST TRUE HERMIT.

00:49.130 --> 00:51.051
♪ RADIO KEEP CRYING BUT... ♪

00:51.051 --> 00:53.094
[ BOTH MOANING ]

00:53.094 --> 00:54.175
[ LAUGHS AND SQUEALS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

00:54.175 --> 00:56.056
30 YEARS WITHOUT THE WARMTH
OF HUMAN TOUCH.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.139
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATING ]

00:58.139 --> 00:59.850
WITHOUT CONVERSATION.

00:59.850 --> 01:01.142
Jo: [ MOANS ]

01:01.142 --> 01:02.393
♪ PEOPLE KEEP JUMPING ♪

01:02.393 --> 01:04.445
[ CELL PHONE CONTINUES
VIBRATING ]
[ LAUGHS ]

01:04.445 --> 01:07.108
THE HERMIT FELT MORE LONELY
WHEN HE WAS OUT IN THE WORLD...

01:07.108 --> 01:08.949
ALEX! ALEX!

01:08.949 --> 01:12.323
THAN HE EVER FELT
IN THE WOODS BY HIMSELF.
[ SQUEALS ]

01:12.323 --> 01:15.656
♪ HEARTS KEEP ON BREAKING,
SOULS KEEP ON ACHING ♪

01:15.656 --> 01:17.498
♪ BUT I NEVER
BEEN IN LOVE BEFORE ♪

01:17.498 --> 01:20.911
SURROUNDED BY PEOPLE
BUT DROWNING IN SOLITUDE...

01:22.663 --> 01:24.665
THAT KIND OF LONELINESS?

01:24.665 --> 01:26.046
♪ YEAH, YEAH, OH, OH ♪

01:26.046 --> 01:31.762
♪♪♪

01:31.762 --> 01:32.883
♪ OH, OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH ♪

01:32.883 --> 01:34.475
CAN SWALLOW YOU WHOLE.

01:34.475 --> 01:36.427
[ MACHINE WHIRRING ]

01:36.427 --> 01:39.059
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

01:39.059 --> 01:41.392
HEY! I TEXTED YOU.

01:41.392 --> 01:43.023
YEAH, I SAW THAT.
I WAS BUSY.

01:43.023 --> 01:44.225
WELL, CRISTINA WOULD'VE
RESPONDED.

01:44.225 --> 01:45.186
THAT'S NOT HOW IT WORKS.

01:45.186 --> 01:47.027
NOT IF SHE WAS DOING
WHAT I WAS DOING.

01:47.027 --> 01:48.779
YOU PAUSE. THAT'S THE RULE.

01:48.779 --> 01:50.401
WHAT?
IF THE TEXT IS URGENT,

01:50.401 --> 01:51.992
CRISTINA WOULD SAY TO OWEN,
"PAUSE,"

01:51.992 --> 01:53.324
AND I WOULD SAY TO DEREK,
"PAUSE,"

01:53.324 --> 01:54.735
THEN WE'D
TEXT EACH OTHER BACK.

01:54.735 --> 01:57.037
IN THE MIDDLE OF SEX?
IF THE THE TEXT IS URGENT.

01:57.037 --> 01:59.119
THE FACT YOU ARE CHECKING A TEXT
WHILE YOU'RE DOING IT

01:59.119 --> 02:01.202
IS ALREADY SAD.
WE HAD A SPECIAL RINGTONE.

02:01.202 --> 02:02.873
HEY, YOU WANT
A SPECIAL RINGTONE?

02:02.873 --> 02:05.456
NO. WAIT, THIS PAUSE THING...

02:05.456 --> 02:07.087
[ LAUGHS ] LIKE, YOUR LEGS
ARE IN THE AIR

02:07.087 --> 02:09.089
AND YOU'RE SCREAMING AND...
PAUSE.

02:09.089 --> 02:11.512
NO, I DON'T PAUSE.
JO DOESN'T PAUSE.

02:11.512 --> 02:13.964
SHE FAST-FORWARDS
AND SHE REWINDS,

02:13.964 --> 02:15.466
BUT SHE DOESN'T PAUSE.
OKAY, THAT'S GROSS.

02:15.466 --> 02:18.219
DO YOU WANNA SCRUB IN
ON MY I.V.C. SARCOMA?
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

02:18.219 --> 02:19.260
IS IT A KID?
NO.

02:19.260 --> 02:20.521
THEN NO. WHY?

02:20.521 --> 02:22.473
BECAUSE I WANT SOME COMPANY.

02:22.473 --> 02:23.724
GET A RESIDENT.

02:23.724 --> 02:26.607
I HAVE A RESIDENT.
I WANT A GROWNUP.
BYE.

02:26.607 --> 02:28.189
CRISTINA WOULD'VE SCRUBBED IN.
YOU'RE NO GOOD AT THIS.

02:28.189 --> 02:29.650
BAILEY!

02:29.650 --> 02:31.482
YOU WANNA SCRUB IN
ON MY I.V.C. SARCOMA?

02:31.482 --> 02:34.195
WELL, YOU DON'T NEED ME FOR
THAT. DON'T YOU HAVE A RESIDENT?

02:34.195 --> 02:36.036
RESIDENTS ARE BORING.
ALL THEY WANNA DO IS LEARN.

02:36.036 --> 02:37.238
COME ON.
IT'S GONNA BE GOOD.

02:37.238 --> 02:39.240
IT'S ALL OVER THE LIVER,
HEPATIC VEIN.

02:39.240 --> 02:40.661
IT'S GONNA BE
BLOODY AND GROSS.

02:40.661 --> 02:42.913
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
DOES LOOK LIKE FUN.

02:42.913 --> 02:46.207
PAGE ME WHEN YOU'RE READY.
SEE YOU IN THE O.R.

02:46.207 --> 02:49.089
ADRIAN NELSON, 51.
PRESENTS WITH ABDOMINAL PAIN.

02:49.089 --> 02:51.632
SCANS SHOW A LEIOMYOSARCOMA

02:51.632 --> 02:53.053
BEHIND THE LIVER,
INCLUDING THE I.V.C.

02:53.053 --> 02:54.555
WHAT'S THE SURGICAL PLAN?

02:54.555 --> 02:56.847
LAPAROTOMY TO ISOLATE
THE VESSEL,

02:56.847 --> 02:59.179
RESECT THE TUMOR,
AND THEN REPLACE WITH A GRAFT.

02:59.179 --> 03:01.562
IT'S A PRETTY STRAIGHTFORWARD
PROCEDURE, ADRIAN.

03:01.562 --> 03:03.103
I DON'T FORESEE ANY PROBLEM.

03:03.103 --> 03:04.725
COULD I ASK YOU TO...

03:04.725 --> 03:07.017
I-IT'S SILLY. NEVER MIND.

03:07.017 --> 03:08.569
Meredith: WHAT IS IT?

03:08.569 --> 03:11.732
SHE WANTS YOU TO --
TO SWEAR ON THE BOOK.

03:11.732 --> 03:13.274
[ HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE ]

03:13.274 --> 03:14.615
"THE ODYSSEY."

03:14.615 --> 03:16.407
IT'S -- IT'S THE FIRST BOOK
I EVER SOLD ADRIAN.

03:16.407 --> 03:17.578
THE DAY WE MET.

03:17.578 --> 03:19.780
MICHAEL'S A RARE BOOK VENDOR.

03:19.780 --> 03:21.532
OUR HANDS TOUCHED
WHEN I WAS RINGING HER UP...
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:21.532 --> 03:23.163
AND IT WAS...[ LAUGHS ]
IT WAS SUCH A HIGH.

03:23.163 --> 03:25.586
IT WAS ELECTRIC.

03:25.586 --> 03:27.127
WE WERE BOTH TOO SHY
TO ASK FOR A DATE.

03:27.127 --> 03:28.999
SO I WROTE MY NUMBER
ON A BOOKMARK.

03:28.999 --> 03:32.253
I SAW IT AS SOON AS I GOT HOME,
AND THEN I CALLED.

03:32.253 --> 03:35.175
WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER EVER SINCE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:35.175 --> 03:38.178
THIS BOOK, IT'S -- IT'S --
IT'S OUR WEDDING RING.

03:38.178 --> 03:41.101
COULD YOU SWEAR ON THE BOOK,
DR. GREY,

03:41.101 --> 03:42.263
THAT YOU'LL DO YOUR BEST?

03:42.263 --> 03:43.474
IT WOULD MEAN SO MUCH.

03:43.474 --> 03:44.725
[ TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE ]

03:44.725 --> 03:46.727
DR. WILSON, TOO.

03:46.727 --> 03:47.938
SURE.
I SWEAR.

03:49.400 --> 03:50.811
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

03:52.192 --> 03:55.776
SO DR. WILSON WILL PREP YOU,
AND I'LL SEE YOU UP THERE.

03:55.776 --> 03:58.198
[ Lowered voice ]
THEY'RE ADORABLE.

03:58.198 --> 04:00.120
THEY'RE WEIRDOS.

04:00.120 --> 04:02.453
[ HEARTBEAT WHOOSHING ]
OKAY, YOU'RE GONNA FEEL
A LITTLE BIT OF PRESSURE.

04:02.453 --> 04:04.535
AND THIS WILL TELL US
CONCLUSIVELY

04:04.535 --> 04:07.207
IF THE OSTEOGENESIS IMPERFECTA
IS TYPE II OR III?

04:07.207 --> 04:08.829
YEAH.
IT'S PROBABLY TYPE II THOUGH,
RIGHT?

04:08.829 --> 04:11.962
I MEAN, SO FAR THERE'S BEEN
NO INDICATION OF FETAL DISTRESS.

04:11.962 --> 04:13.003
WELL, WE'LL KNOW SOON ENOUGH.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.336
[ WHOOSHING CONTINUES ]

04:15.336 --> 04:18.138
IT'LL BE OKAY.
O.I. TYPE III, IT'S HARD, SURE,

04:18.138 --> 04:20.431
WHEN THERE'S SURGERIES AND
CHALLENGES, BUT WE'RE SURGEONS.

04:20.431 --> 04:23.223
WE CAN...WE CAN HANDLE
CHALLENGES, RIGHT?

04:23.223 --> 04:24.645
MM-HMM.
I MEAN, WE'LL --

04:24.645 --> 04:28.188
WE'LL STILL BE ABLE TO GIVE
OUR BABY A WONDERFUL LIFE.

04:28.188 --> 04:29.350
RIGHT?

04:29.350 --> 04:32.693
MANY TYPE III BABIES LIVE
VERY, VERY HAPPY LIVES.

04:36.987 --> 04:38.609
SHOULDN'T DR. HERMAN
BE DOING THIS?

04:38.609 --> 04:40.611
MM, IT'S
VERY ROUTINE PROCEDURE.

04:40.611 --> 04:43.073
DR. HERMAN IS THE BIG GUN.

04:43.073 --> 04:45.576
WE ONLY FIRE THE BIG GUN
WHEN WE NEED THE BIG GUN.

04:45.576 --> 04:47.037
I'M THE LITTLE GUN,
SO...

04:47.037 --> 04:48.789
[ Whispers ]
LET THE LITTLE GUN WORK.

04:50.961 --> 04:55.125
[ WHOOSHING CONTINUES ]

04:59.470 --> 05:02.052
THANK YOU SO MUCH. I KNOW THAT
TOOK UP A LOT OF YOUR TIME.

05:02.052 --> 05:04.014
I JUST WANNA GET
ALL OF THE VIEWS

05:04.014 --> 05:06.186
WITH THE THINNEST CROSS SECTIONS
I CAN GET.

05:06.186 --> 05:08.729
AND I FIND THAT ADORABLE.

05:08.729 --> 05:11.101
YOU REALLY THINK YOU CAN
PULL OFF YOUR PLAN, HUH?

05:11.101 --> 05:13.354
I'VE GOT
ALL YOUR PAST MEDICAL RECORDS.

05:13.354 --> 05:14.735
ONCE I GET A FIRM GRASP

05:14.735 --> 05:17.608
ON THE ROADS YOUR OTHER SURGEONS
TOOK TO GET TO "NO,"

05:17.608 --> 05:19.440
I CAN CUT AWAY A CLEAR PATH
TO "YES."

05:19.440 --> 05:20.941
BY THE TIME I'M DONE
WITH YOUR TUMOR,

05:20.941 --> 05:22.152
I'M GONNA BE ABLE TO TELL YOU

05:22.152 --> 05:23.444
WHAT STREET
THIS BASTARD GREW UP ON

05:23.444 --> 05:25.285
AND WHERE IT LOST ITS VIRGINITY.
HMM.

05:25.285 --> 05:27.327
WELL, YOU CERTAINLY ARE
CONFIDENT.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.450
THANK YOU.
OR DELUSIONAL.

05:29.450 --> 05:31.121
ONE OF THE TWO.

05:31.121 --> 05:34.955
IT'S HARD TO TELL.
THEY LOOK SIMILAR.

05:38.338 --> 05:42.383
SO I THINK WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT WHAT WE'LL DECIDE

05:42.383 --> 05:43.844
IF IT TURNS OUT
THE BABY'S TYPE III.

05:43.844 --> 05:45.466
I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
HE WON'T BE.

05:45.466 --> 05:48.098
YEAH, I KNOW THAT'S WHAT
YOU BELIEVE. SO DO I, OBVIOUSLY.

05:48.098 --> 05:51.351
BUT IF HE IS TYPE II,
THEN IT'S SO TERRIBLE...

05:51.351 --> 05:52.683
I KNOW.
AND FATAL...

05:52.683 --> 05:54.064
[ SIGHS ]
USUALLY.

05:54.064 --> 05:55.436
ALL RIGHT? AND BEFORE THAT,
IT'S EVEN WORSE.

05:55.436 --> 05:58.399
I-I KNOW ALL OF THIS. I JUST --
I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT IT.

05:58.399 --> 06:00.070
BUT WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT IT.
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT IT.

06:00.070 --> 06:03.033
W-WHY? WHY CAN'T WE JUST WAIT
UNTIL TOMORROW?

06:03.033 --> 06:05.696
BECAUSE WE SHOULD HAVE A PLAN.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

06:05.696 --> 06:07.868
OKAY, WELL, UH,
WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO?

06:07.868 --> 06:10.411
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING.
I THINK WE SHOULD DECIDE.

06:10.411 --> 06:12.993
NO, NO. I'M -- I'M --
I'M ASKING WHAT YOU WANT.

06:12.993 --> 06:15.165
I WANT FOR US TO
FIGURE THIS OUT TOGETHER.

06:15.165 --> 06:16.797
I DON'T -- I DON'T THINK
THAT'S TRUE.

06:16.797 --> 06:19.049
I THINK THAT YOU ALREADY KNOW
WHAT YOU WOULD WANNA DO.

06:19.049 --> 06:20.000
SO...
WHAT?

06:20.000 --> 06:22.503
JUST -- YEAH, JUST SAY IT
OUT LOUD.

06:22.503 --> 06:24.675
DON'T...
RIGHT NOW.
WELL, WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO?

06:24.675 --> 06:26.467
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

06:31.181 --> 06:33.974
IF OUR BABY IS TYPE II, I...

06:35.395 --> 06:37.858
I THINK WE SHOULD TERMINATE.

06:40.821 --> 06:44.234
AND I DON'T CARE WHETHER
OUR BABY IS TYPE II OR TYPE III.

06:44.234 --> 06:46.527
[ Voice breaks ] EITHER WAY,
I WANNA KEEP HIM.

06:46.527 --> 06:47.738
WH--APRIL.

06:47.738 --> 06:51.081
I TOLD YOU I DIDN'T WANNA
TALK ABOUT THIS.

06:54.374 --> 06:56.206
Jo: LOOK AT
ALL THESE ADHESIONS.

06:56.206 --> 06:58.038
Miranda: NO WAY
TO SEE 'EM COMING.

06:58.038 --> 07:01.502
SNEAKY LITTLE BASTARDS
WON'T SHOW UP ON THE SCAN.

07:01.502 --> 07:03.003
Meredith: AND THERE'S MORE
OF THEM POSTERIORLY, TOO.

07:03.003 --> 07:04.715
I NEED SOME MORE EXPOSURE.

07:04.715 --> 07:06.176
YOU'RE THINKING OF EXTENDING
THE INCISION?

07:06.176 --> 07:08.258
I HAVE TO. I CAN'T SEE
WHAT'S UP IN THERE.

07:08.258 --> 07:09.890
THIS TUMOR JUST KEEPS COMING.

07:09.890 --> 07:12.432
AND ALL THE LANDMARKS
ARE OBSCURED.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.264
I'M LOST IN HERE.
IT'S LIKE GOING BLIND.

07:14.264 --> 07:16.477
HEY, UH, WOULD YOU BRING
THOSE SCANS CLOSER, PLEASE?

07:16.477 --> 07:17.898
Man: YES, DOCTOR.

07:19.399 --> 07:22.112
SEE, THE TUMOR SHOULD BE
IN THE SUPRAHEPATIC I.V.C. ONLY.

07:22.112 --> 07:23.113
Meredith: THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

07:23.113 --> 07:25.065
IT DOESN'T SHOW
ANY FURTHER LOCAL INVASION.

07:25.065 --> 07:27.447
SHOW ME THE CORONAL VIEW?
[ BEEP ]

07:27.447 --> 07:29.660
WHAT'S THE TUMOR DOING
ALL THE WAY OVER THERE?

07:29.660 --> 07:31.201
THAT'S WHAT I WANT TO KNOW.

07:31.201 --> 07:33.494
HOW OLD ARE THESE SCANS?
THEY'RE ONLY TWO WEEKS OLD.

07:33.494 --> 07:34.995
AND THEY'RE
COMPLETELY OUTDATED.

07:34.995 --> 07:37.037
I MEAN, THIS THING IS GROWING
TOO FAST.

07:37.037 --> 07:38.499
NOTHING IS WHERE
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

07:38.499 --> 07:41.211
TUMOR HAS EXTENDED TO
THE I.V.C. TRIBUTARIES.

07:41.211 --> 07:43.293
YEAH, THESE SCANS ARE USELESS.
I CAN'T SEE WHAT I'M DOING.

07:43.293 --> 07:46.547
OH, GOD. IT'S ALSO SPREADING
THROUGH THE DIAPHRAGM. SUCTION.

07:46.547 --> 07:49.009
I CAN'T EVEN SEE WHERE...
NEITHER CAN I.

07:49.009 --> 07:51.852
DON'T TOUCH THAT. IT'S TEARING.
[ SUCTION GURGLING ]

07:51.852 --> 07:53.854
WELL, THE TUMOR'S EXTENDED ALL
THE WAY UP BETWEEN THE LUNGS.

07:53.854 --> 07:55.145
SOMEONE PAGE CARDIO!

07:55.145 --> 07:56.647
IT'S ALL THE WAY UP INTO
THE PERICARDIUM.

07:56.647 --> 07:58.599
GET THE SUCTION OUT. DON'T TOUCH
IT. DON'T DO ANYTHING.

07:58.599 --> 08:00.150
PAGE -- PAGE CARDIO 9-1-1!

08:00.150 --> 08:02.312
WE GOTTA GET OUT. EVERYBODY OUT.
HANDS OFF.

08:09.279 --> 08:11.031
WHAT ARE WE DOING?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:15.996 --> 08:19.169
CAN SOMEONE SAY SOMETHING?
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

08:19.169 --> 08:21.081
IT'S SPREAD FROM HER MAJOR
BLOOD VESSELS TO HER LIVER,

08:21.081 --> 08:23.253
DIAPHRAGM, PERICARDIUM,
AND MAYBE EVEN HER HEART.

08:23.253 --> 08:25.676
HOW CAN ONE TUMOR
GROW THIS BIG THIS FAST?

08:25.676 --> 08:27.588
IT IS EVERYWHERE.
IT'S A MONSTER.

08:27.588 --> 08:28.929
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

08:31.592 --> 08:33.724
I HAVE NO IDEA.

08:49.279 --> 08:50.951
Meredith: MICHAEL,
I'M AFRAID ADRIAN'S TUMOR

08:50.951 --> 08:52.242
HAS GROWN CONSIDERABLY

08:52.242 --> 08:54.494
AND IT'S NOW REACHING AROUND
HER HEART.

08:54.494 --> 08:56.036
SO DR. PIERCE IS HERE.

08:56.036 --> 08:57.578
HER -- HER H-HEART?

08:57.578 --> 08:59.870
IT'S ENTANGLED THROUGH THE VEIN
THAT STRETCHES UP

08:59.870 --> 09:02.082
FROM HER LIVER TO HER HEART.

09:02.082 --> 09:04.254
AND IT'S GROWING MORE RAPIDLY
THAN ANTICIPATED.

09:04.254 --> 09:07.047
SO WE NEED TO TAKE HER
FOR MORE M.R.I.s

09:07.047 --> 09:10.340
SO WE CAN SEE HOW EXTENSIVE
THE TUMOR'S GROWTH IS.

09:10.340 --> 09:12.262
NOW THERE'S ALL OF YOU.

09:12.262 --> 09:15.135
THREE DOCTORS.

09:15.135 --> 09:17.017
[ Voice breaks ]
THREE IS A LOT.

09:20.230 --> 09:24.234
LOOK, UM, ODYSSEUS DIDN'T RETURN
TO ITHACA ALL BY HIMSELF.

09:24.234 --> 09:27.608
HE NEEDED A LOT OF HELP, RIGHT,
FROM THE PHAEACIANS?

09:27.608 --> 09:29.610
WELL, WE'RE THE PHAEACIANS.

09:29.610 --> 09:32.402
YOU WANT ALL THE PHAEACIANS
YOU CAN GET.

09:32.402 --> 09:34.825
WE ARE GOING TO FIGURE
THIS TUMOR OUT.

09:37.157 --> 09:38.408
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

09:38.408 --> 09:39.660
OH.

09:39.660 --> 09:41.201
MMM! SO LIGHT.

09:41.201 --> 09:42.833
AND IT'S LAST YEAR'S MODEL.

09:42.833 --> 09:45.706
WE'RE WEEKS AWAY FROM UNVEILING
ONE THAT WILL WEIGH 30% LESS.

09:45.706 --> 09:47.207
MM.
WOW. VERY IMPRESSIVE.

09:47.207 --> 09:49.299
[ CHUCKLES ] YOUR PROJECT
IS IMPRESSIVE.

09:49.299 --> 09:51.381
ROBOTIC LIMBS
FOR INJURED VETS?

09:51.381 --> 09:52.883
SEXY AS HELL.

09:52.883 --> 09:56.807
AND WE AT CyberSystems ARE DYING
TO CLIMB INTO BED WITH YOU.

09:56.807 --> 09:58.679
WELL, THAT'S VERY FLATTERING.

09:58.679 --> 10:00.430
Owen: MM-HMM.
GOOD. I WANT IT TO BE.

10:00.430 --> 10:01.982
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
I'LL LEAVE YOU THIS FOLDER

10:01.982 --> 10:04.064
SO YOU CAN GO OVER
THE MATERIALS.

10:04.064 --> 10:05.435
I'LL BE IN SEATTLE
ANOTHER DAY,

10:05.435 --> 10:08.859
SO PLEASE, CALL ME
IF YOU NEED...ANYTHING.

10:08.859 --> 10:12.152
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU FOR COMING IN.

10:13.193 --> 10:15.195
SO...[ SIGHS ]
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

10:15.195 --> 10:16.997
I THINK YOU SHOULD DEFINITELY
GO FOR IT.
REALLY?

10:16.997 --> 10:18.999
'CAUSE I WAS NOT THAT IMPRESSED
WITH THESE TRANSDUCERS.

10:18.999 --> 10:20.200
WHAT? NO.

10:20.200 --> 10:21.451
NO, THOSE --
THOSE THINGS ARE CRAP.

10:21.451 --> 10:23.043
I'M TALKING ABOUT HER.

10:23.043 --> 10:25.666
HER VIBES?
YOU DIDN'T FEEL HER VIBES?

10:25.666 --> 10:28.548
MAJOR VIBAGE
FOR MAJOR HUNT.

10:28.548 --> 10:30.130
[ SCOFFS ] YOU READ THAT
TOTALLY WRONG.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.421
OH, PLEASE.

10:31.421 --> 10:33.343
[ Breathy voice ]
"YOUR PROJECT'S SEXY AS HELL.

10:33.343 --> 10:35.886
OOH, OOH,
LET'S CLIMB INTO BED."

10:35.886 --> 10:36.967
I WAS ACTUALLY UNCOMFORTABLE.

10:36.967 --> 10:38.058
STOP IT!
[ GIGGLES ]

10:39.519 --> 10:41.682
THERE YOU ARE.
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

10:41.682 --> 10:43.603
I WAS PERFORMING A C.V.S.
ON APRIL KEPNER.

10:43.603 --> 10:44.815
WE'RE JUST WAITING
FOR THE RESULTS.

10:44.815 --> 10:45.976
[ Whispers ]
GOD, I HATE WAITING.

10:45.976 --> 10:47.107
IN PEDS, IT IS --
IT'S MUCH EASIER.

10:47.107 --> 10:48.729
YOU KNOW,
THE PARENTS ARE RIGHT THERE.

10:48.729 --> 10:49.940
AND -- AND YOU TALK TO THEM,

10:49.940 --> 10:50.981
AND THEN THEIR KID
IS RIGHT THERE,

10:50.981 --> 10:53.573
SO THEY CAN HOLD THEM CLOSE
AND HOPE FOR THE BEST.

10:53.573 --> 10:54.825
THE CAT'S ON THE ROOF.

10:54.825 --> 10:56.196
WITH THIS,
THERE'S NO KID TO HOLD.

10:56.196 --> 10:58.488
THE PROBLEM FEELS
SO THEORETICAL.

10:58.488 --> 10:59.950
YOU KNOW, THERE'S NO CAT,
THERE'S NO ROOF.

10:59.950 --> 11:02.202
THERE'S JUST TWO SCARED PARENTS
FEELING TOTALLY HELPLESS.

11:02.202 --> 11:03.623
AND YOU'VE HAD
THE RESULTS RUSHED?

11:03.623 --> 11:05.585
[ SIGHS ] YEAH. I SHOULD
GET THEM IN, LIKE, 24 HOURS.

11:05.585 --> 11:07.708
WELL, THEN THERE'S NOTHING MORE
TO DO ABOUT IT TODAY,

11:07.708 --> 11:09.049
WHICH IS GOOD.

11:09.049 --> 11:10.921
I HAVE BEEN WORKING MIRACLES.

11:10.921 --> 11:15.295
I HAVE FOUND US
THE MOST INCREDIBLE SURGERIES,

11:15.295 --> 11:17.177
ALL FOR THE NEXT FEW WEEKS.

11:17.177 --> 11:19.559
LOOK, A T.T.T.S.
IN A 19-WEEKER.

11:19.559 --> 11:22.933
A 21-WEEK T.R.A.P. SEQUENCE
THAT NEEDS AN R.F.A.

11:22.933 --> 11:25.105
A UNILATERAL
PULMONARY AGENESIS.

11:25.105 --> 11:26.857
AND THAT IS JUST
THE BEGINNING.

11:26.857 --> 11:29.399
THE BEGINNING OF WHAT?
YOUR CRASH COURSE.

11:29.399 --> 11:32.442
I HAVE HUNTED DOWN
THE MOST SCREWED UP,

11:32.442 --> 11:34.985
MEDICALLY COMPROMISED FETUSES
THAT I COULD FIND,

11:34.985 --> 11:37.077
AND I'M BRINGING THEM ALL HERE
TO THIS HOSPITAL

11:37.077 --> 11:39.279
FOR YOU TO LEARN
AND US TO SAVE.

11:39.279 --> 11:40.871
AND YOU'LL GET
TO FIX THEM ALL?

11:40.871 --> 11:42.122
WE WILL.

11:42.122 --> 11:43.623
START READING.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.247
YOU CAN THANK ME LATER.

11:50.130 --> 11:51.832
MM.

11:53.713 --> 11:55.675
...AND THEN -- AND THIS SOUNDS
CRAZY, I KNOW, SO DON'T EVEN --

11:55.675 --> 11:57.387
I'LL -- I'LL BUILD IN
A DISTRIBUTION

11:57.387 --> 12:00.300
OF A RADIOACTIVE SEED
DURING SURGERY,

12:00.300 --> 12:03.053
KEEPING DR. HERMAN'S TUMOR BED
FREE OF RECURRING CELLS.

12:03.053 --> 12:04.684
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
USE A LASER.

12:04.684 --> 12:06.937
I AM. I ALREADY DID.
WE'RE WAY PAST THAT.

12:06.937 --> 12:08.108
Richard: TRY AND KEEP UP.

12:08.108 --> 12:10.901
UH, I'M SORRY, SHEPHERD,
BUT THIS IS A GREAT OPPORTUNITY

12:10.901 --> 12:12.522
FOR THEM TO LEARN.
I KNOW. IT'S FINE.

12:12.522 --> 12:15.235
THE LASER IS FOR ABLATING CELLS
OFF THE OPTIC NERVE --

12:15.235 --> 12:16.947
IT'S A MASSIVE
BUTTERFLY GLIOMA.

12:16.947 --> 12:20.030
WELL, IT'S NOT JUST MASSIVE.
I MEAN...

12:20.030 --> 12:21.491
IT'S MAGNIFICENT.
NO, NO, NO.

12:21.491 --> 12:23.994
I-I MEAN THAT,
WON'T A LASER TAKE MONTHS?

12:23.994 --> 12:26.496
A-AGAIN, UH, BEFORE THAT,
I'LL BE USING

12:26.496 --> 12:28.128
THE ULTRASONIC
SURGICAL ASPIRATOR

12:28.128 --> 12:29.249
TO MUSH AND FLUSH THE CELLS,

12:29.249 --> 12:31.751
THEN THE SEXY LASER AND THE --
YEAH.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.083
I'M SORRY. I'M JUST LOST.

12:33.083 --> 12:34.084
UM, YOU WERE JUST TALKING ABOUT
LASER ABLATION.

12:34.084 --> 12:35.755
SO IS THAT CONFINED TO
THE OPTIC CHIASM

12:35.755 --> 12:38.008
OR WILL THAT EXTEND --
GUYS, STEP BACK.

12:38.008 --> 12:42.182
LOOK AT THE WHOLE BIG,
BEAUTIFUL, SHAPELY THING.

12:42.182 --> 12:46.056
EVERY PART OF THIS TUMOR'S BODY
WILL RESPOND DIFFERENTLY.

12:46.056 --> 12:48.058
YOU WILL NEED A MULTITUDE
OF APPROACHES.

12:48.058 --> 12:50.230
YOU WILL HAVE TO BE GENTLE
WITH ONE PART

12:50.230 --> 12:51.521
AND ROUGH WITH THE OTHER.

12:51.521 --> 12:53.733
THAT IS THE ONLY WAY
SHE WILL RESPOND.

12:53.733 --> 12:55.065
GET IT?

12:55.065 --> 12:56.776
I DON'T SEE TUMORS
THE WAY SHE DOES.

12:56.776 --> 12:58.608
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
DIDN'T FIVE SURGEONS SAY

12:58.608 --> 13:01.401
ANY ONE OF THESE APPROACHES
WOULD LIKELY KILL THE PATIENT?

13:01.401 --> 13:03.243
SIX.

13:03.243 --> 13:06.116
BUT NONE OF THEM TRIED IT ALL
AT THE SAME TIME.

13:06.116 --> 13:07.207
IT SHOULD WORK.

13:07.207 --> 13:09.870
MAYBE WE SHOULD START OVER AGAIN
FROM THE BEGINNING.

13:09.870 --> 13:12.212
OKAY.

13:12.212 --> 13:15.675
I WILL BEGIN WITH
A, UH, BIFRONTAL APPROACH.

13:15.675 --> 13:18.008
I-IS THAT THE RIGHT ATRIUM?
I CAN'T TELL.

13:18.008 --> 13:20.180
EVERYTHING LOOKS LIKE MUSH.

13:20.180 --> 13:22.012
WELL, LOOK AT THIS ANGLE
RIGHT HERE.

13:22.012 --> 13:23.383
IS THAT INVADING
THE RIGHT ATRIUM?

13:23.383 --> 13:24.684
I THINK THAT'S
A MOTION ARTIFACT.

13:24.684 --> 13:26.636
CRAP.
ADRIAN'S BACK IN HER ROOM.

13:26.636 --> 13:28.688
STABLE FOR NOW.
HOW WE DOING HERE?

13:28.688 --> 13:30.891
HAS THE CYCLOPS
REVEALED HIMSELF?

13:30.891 --> 13:32.022
THE CYCLOPS?

13:32.022 --> 13:33.483
WELL, THE PATIENT'S A FAN
OF "THE ODYSSEY,"

13:33.483 --> 13:35.195
SO I'M CALLING THE TUMOR
THE CYCLOPS

13:35.195 --> 13:37.197
'CAUSE IT'S A BIG,
UGLY MONSTER.

13:37.197 --> 13:39.439
AND I FEEL LIKE I'M WORKING
WITH ONE EYE

13:39.439 --> 13:41.151
BECAUSE I CAN SEE IT,
BUT I CAN'T GET A SENSE

13:41.151 --> 13:42.742
OF THE WHOLE THING.

13:42.742 --> 13:44.034
EVERY VIEW IS INCOMPLETE.

13:44.034 --> 13:48.118
OKAY, WHAT IF WE GET A NEW SET
OF SCANS, WITH CONTRAST,

13:48.118 --> 13:50.120
THIS TIME WITH
3-D RECONSTRUCTION?

13:50.120 --> 13:51.541
WELL, THE WOMAN'S LYING OPEN
IN HER BED.

13:51.541 --> 13:53.213
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR A LOT OF TRIAL AND ERROR.

13:53.213 --> 13:55.085
I JUST WANNA REACH IN
AND GRAB IT.

13:55.085 --> 13:58.718
WELL, WE COULD GO IN WITH THESE,
BUT, YEAH, I CAN'T SEE.

13:59.920 --> 14:01.962
IF I COULD JUST
HOLD IT IN MY HAND

14:01.962 --> 14:04.174
SO THAT I COULD SEE IT...

14:04.174 --> 14:05.135
HOLY CRAP.

14:05.135 --> 14:07.677
WHAT?
SHE'S HAVING AN IDEA.

14:07.677 --> 14:09.469
I ALREADY HAD IT LAST YEAR,
AND IT'S BRILLIANT.

14:09.469 --> 14:12.232
[ TYPING ]
WE ARE GOING TO PRINT IT.

14:12.232 --> 14:13.353
THE WHOLE TUMOR.

14:13.353 --> 14:14.564
I TRIED IT
WITH THE PORTAL VEINS,

14:14.564 --> 14:15.815
BUT IT'S NOT WORKING.

14:15.815 --> 14:18.108
BUT WITH THIS, WE DON'T NEED IT
TO FUNCTION.

14:18.108 --> 14:19.479
SHE'S GOT A FUNCTIONING TUMOR.

14:19.479 --> 14:21.361
[ BEEP ]
WE JUST NEED TO BE ABLE
TO SEE IT

14:21.361 --> 14:23.653
SO WE KNOW HOW TO KILL IT.
KNOW YOUR ENEMY.

14:23.653 --> 14:25.075
IS THIS GONNA WORK?
IT'LL WORK.

14:25.075 --> 14:26.326
OOH, 2% LEFT TO UPLOAD.

14:26.326 --> 14:27.948
THIS IS HOW WE BEAT THIS THING.

14:27.948 --> 14:30.040
THIS IS HOW WE GET
VISUALIZATION.

14:30.040 --> 14:34.204
WE ARE GOING TO HAVE A TANGIBLE,
ANATOMICALLY CORRECT

14:34.204 --> 14:37.167
3-D MODEL OF THIS EXACT TUMOR,

14:37.167 --> 14:38.708
AND CORRELATE TO
THE ADJACENT ORGANS --

14:38.708 --> 14:40.550
DONE!
LOADED! [ LAUGHS ]

14:40.550 --> 14:43.553
[ PRINTER WHIRRING ]

14:53.813 --> 14:57.607
IN 10 HOURS.

14:58.939 --> 15:02.072
THE LONGEST DOCUMENTED SURVIVING
TYPE II CASE THAT I COULD FIND

15:02.072 --> 15:03.823
LIVED FOR ALL OF 18 MONTHS.

15:03.823 --> 15:05.615
IN AN I.C.U. HIS ENTIRE LIFE,

15:05.615 --> 15:07.988
HOOKED UP TO A FEEDING TUBES
AND A VENTILATOR.

15:07.988 --> 15:09.329
THAT'S NOT A LIFE.

15:09.329 --> 15:11.031
THAT'S NOT A LIFE I WANT
FOR MY SON.

15:11.031 --> 15:13.533
I -- OF C--
NEITHER DO I. I...

15:13.533 --> 15:15.585
OKAY. SO THEN HOW CAN YOU --

15:15.585 --> 15:17.417
BECAUSE WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT WILL HAPPEN.

15:17.417 --> 15:19.589
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF HE'S TYPE II.

15:19.589 --> 15:21.711
OKAY, BUT WHAT IF HE IS?

15:21.711 --> 15:23.633
[ Whispers ] ANY AMOUNT OF TIME
THAT HE SURVIVES...

15:23.633 --> 15:25.045
ANY AMOUNT OF TIME THAT HE LIVES
WILL BE --

15:25.045 --> 15:26.716
WILL BE WITH US,

15:26.716 --> 15:27.927
IN OUR ARMS...
YES.

15:27.927 --> 15:30.220
KNOWING THAT HE'S LOVED
AND WANTED.

15:30.220 --> 15:32.432
AND HIS BONES CAN BREAK
IF YOU TOUCH HIM.

15:32.432 --> 15:34.514
HIS BONES CAN BREAK
IF WE'RE CHANGING HIS DIAPER.

15:34.514 --> 15:36.056
WE'RE DOCTORS.
WE CAN HANDLE IT.

15:36.056 --> 15:37.767
IF -- IF ANYONE CAN HANDLE IT,
WE CAN.

15:37.767 --> 15:39.189
I'M NOT SAYING
WE CAN'T HANDLE IT.

15:39.189 --> 15:40.480
I'M ASKING IF WE SHOULD.

15:40.480 --> 15:41.982
YEAH, WE'RE DOCTORS.

15:41.982 --> 15:44.114
MAYBE WE ARE BETTER EQUIPPED TO
MAKE AN EDUCATED DECISION HERE.

15:44.114 --> 15:46.776
AND MAYBE WE WERE
GIVEN THIS BABY FOR A REASON.

15:46.776 --> 15:48.528
Karen: APRIL.

15:48.528 --> 15:50.070
[ SIGHS ]

15:50.070 --> 15:51.201
YOU CALLED YOUR MOM.

15:51.201 --> 15:54.034
YEAH. PEOPLE NEED THEIR MOM
IN A CRISIS.

15:54.034 --> 15:56.206
NO, NOT EVERYBODY DOES.

15:56.206 --> 15:59.039
I CAME AS SOON AS I GOT
YOUR CALL, SWEETIE.

15:59.039 --> 16:01.881
IT'S OKAY.
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

16:01.881 --> 16:04.084
I'M HERE.

16:04.084 --> 16:05.385
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

16:05.385 --> 16:07.427
ARE YOU WORKING TODAY?

16:07.427 --> 16:09.759
NO.
THEN LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

16:09.759 --> 16:11.511
YOU COULD USE
A CHANGE OF SCENERY.

16:11.511 --> 16:12.552
THAT'S ACTUALLY
A REALLY GOOD IDEA.

16:12.552 --> 16:14.144
WE SHOULD TAKE THE DAY,

16:14.144 --> 16:16.356
GO SOMEWHERE NICE,
MAYBE DRIVE TO THE OCEAN.

16:16.356 --> 16:17.977
LET'S GO TO CHURCH.

16:17.977 --> 16:20.230
YOU'LL FIND COMFORT THERE.

16:20.230 --> 16:21.861
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

16:21.861 --> 16:23.943
YEAH, GO AHEAD.

16:23.943 --> 16:25.735
LET'S GO PRAY.

16:37.287 --> 16:38.958
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

16:38.958 --> 16:41.501
[ MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY ]

16:41.501 --> 16:44.003
SHE IS DOING FINE.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.675
THOSE CHAIRS WILL
KILL YOUR BACK.

16:45.675 --> 16:48.088
YOU SHOULD GO HOME
AND GET SOME REST.

16:48.088 --> 16:49.219
I-I CAN'T.

16:49.219 --> 16:54.094
I-I CAN'T GO HOME ALONE
WHEN SHE'S LIKE THIS.

16:54.094 --> 16:56.846
THOUGHT I'D JUST STAY AND READ.

16:56.846 --> 16:59.139
OKAY. THAT'S FINE.
[ GLOVES SNAP ]

16:59.139 --> 17:01.141
BUT I CAN'T READ EITHER.

17:01.141 --> 17:04.023
CAN'T CONCENTRATE.

17:04.023 --> 17:07.026
IT'S ODD. I-I'VE -- I'VE NEVER
HAD THAT PROBLEM.

17:07.026 --> 17:10.860
I THINK IT'S BECAUSE...

17:10.860 --> 17:13.032
I DON'T KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

17:13.032 --> 17:15.495
I-I ALWAYS KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

17:15.495 --> 17:17.036
WELL, SHE'S RIGHT HERE.

17:17.036 --> 17:21.421
IT'S JUST AS IF SHE'S ASLEEP
IN THE BED NEXT TO YOU.

17:21.421 --> 17:22.712
NOT REALLY.

17:24.254 --> 17:27.087
[ Voice breaks ]
BECAUSE SHE MIGHT NOT WAKE UP.

17:27.087 --> 17:29.169
I FEEL LIKE...

17:29.169 --> 17:30.550
LIKE SHE'S SAILED AWAY

17:30.550 --> 17:33.093
AND I DON'T KNOW
IF SHE'S COMING BACK.

17:33.093 --> 17:35.595
THAT'S THE FEELING,
YOU KNOW?

17:35.595 --> 17:39.769
MICHAEL, WE ARE WORKING
VERY HARD TO SOLVE THIS.

17:39.769 --> 17:41.441
I KNOW.

17:41.441 --> 17:44.063
I KNOW. I JUST...

17:44.063 --> 17:45.485
I JUST WANT HER TO COME BACK.

17:47.737 --> 17:50.069
I DO, TOO.

17:52.112 --> 17:54.404
THIS H.L.H.S. CASE
SEEMS IMPOSSIBLE.

17:54.404 --> 17:55.695
MOTHER'S PREGNANT
FOR THE THIRD TIME,

17:55.695 --> 17:57.036
AND EACH BABY WAS STILLBORN.

17:57.036 --> 17:58.538
WELL, THIS ONE WILL BE, TOO.

17:58.538 --> 18:00.870
22q11 DELETION?

18:00.870 --> 18:02.122
SHE SHOULD ADOPT.

18:02.122 --> 18:03.333
[ FOLDER CLATTERS ]

18:03.333 --> 18:05.125
NOW THIS ONE, HOWEVER --

18:05.125 --> 18:08.168
TRACHEAL BALLOON OCCLUSION
FOR C.D.H.?

18:08.168 --> 18:09.709
CARD THAT PUPPY.

18:09.709 --> 18:13.052
HOW DO YOU DO THIS WITHOUT --
I MEAN, THESE STORIES ARE AWFUL.

18:13.052 --> 18:14.264
THEY'RE PATIENTS, ROBBINS.

18:14.264 --> 18:16.596
THE MORE YOU FIND,
THE MORE YOU LEARN,

18:16.596 --> 18:17.977
THE MORE WE SAVE.

18:17.977 --> 18:19.269
IT'S AS SIMPLE AS THAT.

18:19.269 --> 18:21.771
YOUR WORK IS MAKING
THESE THREE CATEGORIES --

18:21.771 --> 18:24.274
POSSIBLE, IMPOSSIBLE, MAYBE.

18:24.274 --> 18:27.106
ANY OTHER APPROACH
IS A WASTE OF OUR TIME.

18:27.106 --> 18:29.108
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

18:29.108 --> 18:31.281
Kat Dahlia: ♪ THINK THAT CUPID'S
UP TO SOMETHING ♪

18:31.281 --> 18:33.403
AHH.
[ CLINK ]

18:33.403 --> 18:35.405
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:35.405 --> 18:36.826
OH, WOW.

18:36.826 --> 18:38.117
♪ BUT LATELY
COLOR SEEM SO BRIGHT ♪

18:38.117 --> 18:39.619
HOLY CRAP.

18:39.619 --> 18:40.830
[ GASPS ] IT'S FATE!

18:40.830 --> 18:42.662
LOOK!
IT'S YOUR SEXY TECH REP!

18:42.662 --> 18:44.204
[ High-pitched voice ]
YOUR SEXY TECH REP!

18:44.204 --> 18:46.336
SHE -- SHE'S NOT
MY SEXY ANYTHING.

18:46.336 --> 18:48.047
NOT YET, BUT SHE COULD BE.

18:48.047 --> 18:51.211
[ LAUGHS ] I CAME OUT TONIGHT
WITH YOU TO -- TO UNWIND,

18:51.211 --> 18:52.512
NOT TO...

18:52.512 --> 18:55.175
AND SHE'S A -- SHE'S A TECH REP.
THAT'S A CONFLICT OF INTEREST.

18:55.175 --> 18:56.756
NOT IF WE DON'T BUY
HER TRANSDUCERS.

18:56.756 --> 18:58.308
MM.
THEY'RE JUNK, ANYWAY.

18:58.308 --> 19:01.931
COME ON! YOU GOTTA GET BACK
IN THE SADDLE.

19:01.931 --> 19:03.223
AND SHE'S GOT A NICE SADDLE.

19:03.223 --> 19:04.854
OH, YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]
[ GLASS THUDS ]

19:04.854 --> 19:06.526
WHAT? WHOA. WHOA.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:06.526 --> 19:08.728
AHH.

19:08.728 --> 19:10.029
OKAY, SO LISTEN,

19:10.029 --> 19:12.071
I'M NOT, UH, REALLY GREAT
AT THIS KIND OF THING,

19:12.071 --> 19:13.273
SO I'M JUST GONNA
BLURT IT OUT.

19:13.273 --> 19:14.364
I THINK THAT
YOU WERE INTERESTED

19:14.364 --> 19:16.366
IN MORE THAN
JUST OUR PROGRAM TODAY.

19:16.366 --> 19:17.777
OH, YOU PICKED UP ON THAT?

19:17.777 --> 19:19.989
I WAS RIGHT! HA HA HA!

19:19.989 --> 19:22.582
I KNEW IT! OKAY.
SO THIS SHOULD BE EASY.

19:22.582 --> 19:25.705
OWEN IS A LITTLE BIT SHY,
BUT HE'S A GREAT GUY.

19:25.705 --> 19:28.708
AND, UH...
THE FEELING'S MUTUAL.

19:28.708 --> 19:30.169
SO...

19:30.169 --> 19:31.551
♪ LOVE ♪

19:31.551 --> 19:33.052
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO WHAT DO YOU SAY?

19:33.052 --> 19:34.133
♪ I'M CONFUSED, I'M DAZIN' ♪

19:34.133 --> 19:36.256
I WOULD SAY THAT
THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT HIM

19:36.256 --> 19:39.429
THAT DOESN'T QUITE...
FEEL LIKE HE'S MY TYPE.

19:39.429 --> 19:41.511
WHAT?! NO! HE'S...
[ LAUGHS ]

19:41.511 --> 19:44.013
HE'S VERY ATTRACTIVE. HE'S NICE.
HE'S FUNNY.

19:44.013 --> 19:45.225
PEOPLE LIKE FUNNY, RIGHT?

19:45.225 --> 19:46.476
I MEAN, COME ON.
GIVE HIM A CHANCE.

19:46.476 --> 19:47.727
WHAT ABOUT HIM
ISN'T YOUR TYPE?

19:47.727 --> 19:50.149
HE HAS A PENIS.

19:50.149 --> 19:51.110
[ DOOR BELL JINGLES ]

19:51.110 --> 19:52.692
[ LAUGHS ] OH!

19:52.692 --> 19:55.615
[ CHUCKLES ] OHH.

19:55.615 --> 19:57.277
OH.

19:57.277 --> 19:59.489
WAIT. NO. YOU WERE...

19:59.489 --> 20:01.531
[ SIGHS ]
YOU -- YOU WERE FLIRTY.

20:01.531 --> 20:02.992
I WAS,

20:02.992 --> 20:05.875
BUT NOT WITH HIM.

20:05.875 --> 20:07.206
♪ AGAIN ♪

20:07.206 --> 20:08.628
OH.

20:08.628 --> 20:09.919
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

20:09.919 --> 20:11.090
UM...

20:11.090 --> 20:12.292
WOW.

20:12.292 --> 20:15.174
I AM WILDLY SADDENED
BY MY, UH, INTENSE...

20:15.174 --> 20:16.546
[ LAUGHS ] LACK OF GAME
RIGHT NOW.

20:16.546 --> 20:17.797
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I DIDN'T SEE THAT COMING.

20:17.797 --> 20:19.048
I -- THERE WAS A TIME
WHEN I WOULD'VE BEEN ALL,

20:19.048 --> 20:20.139
"THAT'S RIGHT.
I KNOW IT'S ME."

20:20.139 --> 20:23.102
BUT RIGHT NOW,
I'M JUST LIKE, UH,

20:23.102 --> 20:25.224
"UH..." [ LAUGHS ]

20:25.224 --> 20:27.347
'CAUSE, UH, YOU LOOKING AT ME
LIKE THAT...[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

20:27.347 --> 20:29.228
YOU ARE GORGEOUS, BY THE WAY.
UH...

20:29.228 --> 20:30.480
DO PEOPLE JUST TELL YOU THAT
ALL THE TIME?

20:30.480 --> 20:31.941
[ LAUGHING ]
BECAUSE YOU ARE GORGEOUS.

20:31.941 --> 20:33.653
I'M NOT.

20:33.653 --> 20:35.114
AM I?

20:35.114 --> 20:36.065
NO.

20:36.065 --> 20:37.987
AM I?

20:37.987 --> 20:41.571
NO. WAIT. NO, NO. WAIT, WAIT.
STOP. STOP, STOP, STOP, STOP.

20:41.571 --> 20:42.912
NOT INTO WOMEN?

20:42.912 --> 20:43.993
NO, NO, NO. I AM, TOTALLY.

20:43.993 --> 20:45.325
WOMEN. MEN. PEOPLE, REALLY.

20:45.325 --> 20:46.706
I'M JUST -- I'M JUST --
I'M JUST --

20:46.706 --> 20:48.127
I'M JUST NOT REALLY SHOPPING
RIGHT NOW.

20:48.127 --> 20:50.169
I'M -- I'M DIVORCED.

20:50.169 --> 20:54.083
AND IT'S...[ CHUCKLES ]
WAS RECENT AND PAINFUL

20:54.083 --> 20:55.425
AND BRUTAL.

20:55.425 --> 20:57.547
BRUTAL, ACTUALLY.

20:57.547 --> 20:58.928
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

20:58.928 --> 21:01.721
WELL, IF YOU WANNA FORGET
FOR JUST A LITTLE WHILE,

21:01.721 --> 21:03.763
I FLY OUT TOMORROW.

21:03.763 --> 21:07.056
DOESN'T HAVE TO BE ANYTHING MORE
THAN ONE NIGHT.

21:07.056 --> 21:09.809
I WOULD LOVE...

21:09.809 --> 21:11.060
♪ I THINK I'M IN LOVE ♪

21:11.060 --> 21:12.852
I WOULD LOVE TO LOVE THAT.
I'M JUST NOT READY.

21:12.852 --> 21:14.394
I'M -- I'M SO SORRY.

21:14.394 --> 21:17.026
♪ I THINK I'M IN LOVE ♪

21:17.026 --> 21:19.489
♪ I THINK I'M IN LOVE ♪

21:19.489 --> 21:20.990
W--

21:20.990 --> 21:22.742
♪ AGAIN ♪

21:25.164 --> 21:26.496
[ KNOCKS ON DOOR ]

21:26.496 --> 21:28.077
HI, GUYS.
HEY.

21:28.077 --> 21:29.038
YOU'RE HERE LATE.

21:29.038 --> 21:30.750
WELL, WE'RE ON A TIMELINE.

21:30.750 --> 21:33.122
I, UH, WAS TAKING A LOOK
AT DR. WALL'S NOTES,

21:33.122 --> 21:34.834
AND I FOUND
SOME CONTRADICTORY INFORMATION.

21:34.834 --> 21:36.506
HE WAS THE SECOND OPINION?

21:36.506 --> 21:38.378
WALL IS WHERE?

21:38.378 --> 21:39.969
CASE WESTERN.

21:39.969 --> 21:41.180
UH, HE WAS THIRD.

21:41.180 --> 21:42.131
MM.
HE'S RADIATION.

21:42.131 --> 21:44.684
RIGHT. JUST GETTING MY DATES
STRAIGHT.

21:44.684 --> 21:46.386
WHAT ARE ALL THESE?

21:46.386 --> 21:48.227
CASES. FETUSES.

21:48.227 --> 21:50.309
EACH CARD REPRESENTS A FETUS
THAT I'M GONNA

21:50.309 --> 21:51.641
TEACH ROBBINS HOW TO FIX.

21:51.641 --> 21:55.985
THAT I...ESTIMATE WE CAN GET TO
IN THE TIME I HAVE.

21:55.985 --> 21:58.358
AND THOSE?
UH, THESE?

21:58.358 --> 22:01.361
NO. THESE ARE THE ONES
THAT I COULD SAVE,

22:01.361 --> 22:03.703
UH, IF I HAD TIME.

22:03.703 --> 22:06.536
YOU SHOULD JUST THINK OF THEM
AS BABIES WHO WILL DIE

22:06.536 --> 22:08.077
IF IT TURNS OUT
THAT YOU'RE FULL OF CRAP

22:08.077 --> 22:09.869
AND CAN'T TAKE OUT MY TUMOR.

22:09.869 --> 22:13.212
AH. NO PRESSURE.

22:13.212 --> 22:15.084
OH, NO. PRESSURE.

22:15.084 --> 22:17.296
WE'RE --
WE'RE ON A TIMELINE HERE, RIGHT?

22:17.296 --> 22:19.048
TRY BEING ME.

22:25.765 --> 22:27.346
OKAY. [ CHUCKLES ]

22:28.388 --> 22:30.059
Woman: DR. MEADOWS,
LABOR AND DELIVERY.

22:30.059 --> 22:32.472
DR. MEADOWS,
LABOR AND DELIVERY.

22:32.472 --> 22:35.775
[ SIREN WAILING ]

22:37.817 --> 22:39.979
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

22:39.979 --> 22:41.901
OH, GOOD! YOU'RE HOME!

22:41.901 --> 22:43.983
JUST IN TIME FOR DINNER.

22:43.983 --> 22:45.695
SMELLS GOOD.

22:45.695 --> 22:47.657
HOW WAS CHURCH?

22:47.657 --> 22:49.158
[ GASPS ] THE CHOIR WAS THERE,

22:49.158 --> 22:51.951
PRACTICING FOR THEIR SERVICE
TOMORROW NIGHT.

22:51.951 --> 22:54.083
REALLY BEAUTIFUL.
WE SHOULD ALL GO TO IT.

22:54.083 --> 22:55.334
AH, I DON'T THINK

22:55.334 --> 22:58.297
WE'LL KNOW WHAT WE'LL BE UP FOR
TOMORROW, KAREN.

22:58.297 --> 23:01.340
BECAUSE OF THE TEST RESULTS?

23:01.340 --> 23:05.094
APRIL TOLD ME ABOUT THE TEST,
AND I TOLD HER

23:05.094 --> 23:07.637
THERE'S REALLY NO POINT
IN EVEN GETTING THOSE RESULTS.

23:07.637 --> 23:08.848
EXCUSE ME?

23:08.848 --> 23:10.640
GOD GIVES
WHAT HE WANTS TO GIVE.

23:10.640 --> 23:13.012
NO TEST IS GOING TO CHANGE THAT.

23:13.012 --> 23:16.315
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]
AND APRIL'S ALREADY SO UPSET,
SO STRESSED.

23:16.315 --> 23:18.107
IT'S NOT GOOD FOR THE BABY.

23:18.107 --> 23:21.320
JUST FOCUS ON LOVING
THAT SWEET LITTLE BABY.

23:21.320 --> 23:23.282
THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

23:23.282 --> 23:25.655
NO, THAT'S DEFINITELY NOT
ALL THAT MATTERS.

23:25.655 --> 23:26.866
I KNOW.

23:26.866 --> 23:28.407
IT'S HARD TO UNDERSTAND
SOMETIMES

23:28.407 --> 23:30.029
HOW HIS PLAN WILL UNFOLD.

23:30.029 --> 23:32.371
YEAH, BUT I'M NOT WORRIED
ABOUT HIS PLAN, AM I?

23:32.371 --> 23:33.743
I'M WORRIED ABOUT OUR PLAN.

23:33.743 --> 23:35.955
HE NEVER GIVES US
MORE THAN WE CAN HANDLE.

23:35.955 --> 23:37.206
GETTING THE RESULTS,

23:37.206 --> 23:39.128
BEING INFORMED ABOUT
OUR BABY'S CONDITION --

23:39.128 --> 23:40.129
THAT'S HOW WE HANDLE IT.

23:40.129 --> 23:41.881
I CALLED OUR PASTOR AT HOME.

23:41.881 --> 23:44.133
APRIL SPOKE TO HIM AT LENGTH.
HE WAS VERY HELPFUL.

23:44.133 --> 23:45.675
APRIL.

23:45.675 --> 23:47.927
ME. LET ME HELP YOU.

23:47.927 --> 23:49.809
[ SIGHS ] WHATEVER HAPPENS,
WE WILL SHOULDER THE BURDEN

23:49.809 --> 23:51.010
WHEN IT IS PLACED UPON US.

23:51.010 --> 23:52.011
WE WILL.

23:52.011 --> 23:53.352
YOU AND I.
WE'LL SHOULDER THE BURDEN.

23:53.352 --> 23:55.054
SHE'S JUST TRYING TO HELP.

23:55.054 --> 23:57.477
IS SHE, THOUGH?
REALLY? IS SHE HELPING?

23:57.477 --> 23:59.188
DON'T SNAP AT HER.

23:59.188 --> 24:01.020
DON'T TALK TO HER IN THAT TONE.
WHAT TONE?

24:01.020 --> 24:02.902
I'M NOT TALKING USING A TONE.
I'M TRYING TO UNDERSTAND.

24:02.902 --> 24:04.063
YOU'RE TRYING TO TALK
MY LITTLE GIRL

24:04.063 --> 24:07.196
INTO DOING SOMETHING
SHE KNOWS IN HER HEART AND SOUL

24:07.196 --> 24:08.117
SHE DOES NOT WANT TO DO.

24:08.117 --> 24:09.659
I'M NOT TRYING TO TALK HER
INTO ANYTHING.

24:09.659 --> 24:11.871
I'M SUPPORTING HER IN TRYING TO
MAKE THE BEST CHOICE POSSIBLE

24:11.871 --> 24:13.282
FOR OUR BABY, FOR HER,
FOR OUR FAMILY.

24:13.282 --> 24:15.495
THIS IS BETWEEN APRIL
AND HER GOD.
[ SCOFFS ] OKAY.

24:15.495 --> 24:18.457
AND IF YOU THINK
SHE IS GOING TO AGREE

24:18.457 --> 24:20.169
TO ABORT HER CHILD...
OUR CHILD!

24:20.169 --> 24:21.921
YOU ARE --
GET THAT STRAIGHT.
IT'S OUR CHILD.

24:21.921 --> 24:24.383
STOP IT! STOP IT!
STOP IT! STOP IT!

24:24.383 --> 24:26.676
NONE OF THIS IS HELPING!

24:26.676 --> 24:28.678
YOU ARE NOT HELPING,
NEITHER OF YOU.

24:28.678 --> 24:30.009
I AM STANDING HERE,

24:30.009 --> 24:31.931
LISTENING TO YOU TELL ME THAT
GOD ONLY GIVES ME ONE CHOICE,

24:31.931 --> 24:34.894
AND YOU TELLING ME THAT I SHOULD
FORGO GOD'S CHOICE.

24:34.894 --> 24:37.056
AND THE TRUTH IS,
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING

24:37.056 --> 24:41.400
EXPECT THAT I AM SCARED AND SAD
AND I'M ALONE.

24:41.400 --> 24:43.362
YOU'RE BOTH JUST STANDING THERE,

24:43.362 --> 24:45.024
YELLING AT EACH OTHER
AND TALKING AT ME,

24:45.024 --> 24:49.068
BUT I AM ALONE,
AND IT IS TERRIFYING!

24:49.068 --> 24:51.531
AND THE LOUDER YOU GET,
THE MORE TERRIFIED I BECOME,

24:51.531 --> 24:55.164
SO I JUST NEED YOU BOTH
TO JUST SHUT UP!

24:55.164 --> 24:59.078
CAN YOU...
CAN YOU DO THAT?

24:59.078 --> 25:04.213
CAN YOU PLEASE -- CAN YOU PLEASE
BOTH JUST SHUT UP?

25:10.469 --> 25:11.721
[ EXHALES SHAKILY ]

25:17.016 --> 25:19.689
[ SIREN WAILING ]

25:19.689 --> 25:21.100
[ PRINTER CONTINUES WHIRRING ]

25:21.100 --> 25:23.102
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
STILL DOING HERE?

25:23.102 --> 25:26.025
WE'RE SOLVING A TUMOR
BY 3-D PRINTING IT.

25:26.025 --> 25:27.777
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

25:27.777 --> 25:29.198
WHAT ARE YOU STILL
DOING HERE?

25:29.198 --> 25:31.110
ALSO SOLVING A TUMOR.

25:31.110 --> 25:33.072
MAYBE YOU SHOULD 3-D PRINT
YOUR TUMOR.

25:33.072 --> 25:35.865
[ SIGHS ] VISIBILITY
IS NOT MY PROBLEM.

25:35.865 --> 25:39.829
I CAN SEE MY TUMOR
IN ALL ITS PROBLEMATIC GLORY,

25:39.829 --> 25:41.160
AND IT'S GIVING ME
THE MIDDLE FINGER

25:41.160 --> 25:43.372
IN FRONT OF RICHARD WEBBER
AND A BUNCH OF RESIDENTS.

25:43.372 --> 25:45.044
WHERE ARE THE KIDS?

25:45.044 --> 25:47.086
UPSTAIRS.

25:47.086 --> 25:49.258
DAYCARE. NIGHTCARE.
WHATEVER CARE.

25:49.258 --> 25:50.930
IT'S OPEN 24 HOURS.

25:50.930 --> 25:53.593
YOU KNOW THAT'S ONLY
FOR SURGEONS ON CALL, RIGHT?

25:53.593 --> 25:55.885
BAILEY, DON'T JUDGE ME.
DEREK LIVES IN D.C.

25:55.885 --> 25:58.267
NO,
I'M SAYING IF THEY ASK YOU,

25:58.267 --> 26:00.139
MAKE UP SOMETHING ABOUT
BEING ON CALL.

26:00.139 --> 26:02.772
WHEN I HAD MY GENOME LAB,
I WAS ON CALL TWICE A WEEK.

26:02.772 --> 26:04.273
YOU ALL REALIZE
THAT PRINTING THIS THING

26:04.273 --> 26:06.235
IS GONNA TAKE, LIKE,
FIVE MORE HOURS?

26:06.235 --> 26:07.857
7-ISH.
7 HOURS AND 20 MINUTES.

26:07.857 --> 26:09.358
7 AND A HALF.

26:09.358 --> 26:13.112
I'M JUST SAYING YOU COULD GO
HOME, SLEEP, AND THEN COME BACK.

26:13.112 --> 26:16.195
SOMEONE HAS TO STAY
IN CASE THE PRINTER CRASHES.

26:16.195 --> 26:17.867
[ WHIRRING CONTINUES ]

26:17.867 --> 26:19.659
PLUS, I DON'T MIND.
I LIKE THE SOUND.

26:19.659 --> 26:22.081
IT'S KINDA SOOTHING.

26:22.081 --> 26:23.753
[ SIGHS ]

26:23.753 --> 26:27.466
IT FEELS WEIRD TO SLEEP ALONE.

26:27.466 --> 26:30.469
I'M NOT USED TO IT.
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

26:30.469 --> 26:33.843
HE USED TO GO AWAY
ALL THE TIME,

26:33.843 --> 26:35.845
BUT THIS TIME, HE'S...

26:35.845 --> 26:37.516
HE'S GONE,

26:37.516 --> 26:40.099
AND I KNOW HE'S GONE.

26:40.099 --> 26:41.600
AND THE BED FEELS LONELY.

26:44.724 --> 26:48.107
IT'S LIKE I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO SLEEP ALONE.

26:48.107 --> 26:49.819
YOU DON'T.

26:49.819 --> 26:53.032
I MEAN, BEFORE THREE MONTHS AGO,
ANY TIME I CALLED YOUR HOUSE

26:53.032 --> 26:55.534
OR CAME OVER OR SKYPED
OR WHATEVER,

26:55.534 --> 26:57.156
CRISTINA WAS THERE.

26:57.156 --> 26:58.908
THERE'S NO WAY YOU EVER SLEPT
ALONE. I MEAN, YOU HAD DEREK.

26:58.908 --> 27:00.449
AND IF YOU DIDN'T HAVE DEREK,
YOU HAD CRISTINA.

27:00.449 --> 27:02.912
I'M GUESSING
IF IT CAME DOWN TO IT,

27:02.912 --> 27:05.374
YOU WERE, LIKE, THE MIDDLE SPOON
IN THE MIDDLE OF

27:05.374 --> 27:08.127
A VERY WEIRD
SPOONING SITUATION.

27:10.209 --> 27:12.551
I'VE NEVER MET
A LESS ALONE PERSON

27:12.551 --> 27:14.133
THAN YOU USED...

27:14.133 --> 27:16.635
USED TO BE.

27:19.098 --> 27:22.351
I HAVE TO LEARN
TO SLEEP ALONE.

27:22.351 --> 27:24.974
BEN SNORES.

27:24.974 --> 27:27.396
AND HE SOMETIMES TALKS
IN HIS SLEEP.

27:27.396 --> 27:28.768
AND HE'S HOT.

27:28.768 --> 27:30.109
LIKE...A FURNACE.

27:30.109 --> 27:32.111
LIKE FLAMES SHOOTIN' OUT
OF HIM.

27:32.111 --> 27:34.033
HE'S LUCKY I LOVE HIM.

27:34.033 --> 27:38.117
AND HE'S A RESIDENT
AND HARDLY HOME AT NIGHT.

27:38.117 --> 27:39.488
OR HE'D BE DEAD.

27:39.488 --> 27:42.081
Woman: ♪ I WILL BE YOUR... ♪

27:42.081 --> 27:44.663
I MISS SLEEPING
WITH A MAN IN MY BED.

27:44.663 --> 27:46.495
YOU KNOW,
FACING AWAY FROM EACH OTHER,

27:46.495 --> 27:51.420
BARELY TOUCHING EXPECT FOR JUST
THE ARM THROWN OVER YOUR WAIST.

27:51.420 --> 27:53.252
WHEN I'D WAKE UP AT NIGHT,

27:53.252 --> 27:56.055
TERRIFIED OF...

27:56.055 --> 27:58.217
ME,

27:58.217 --> 28:00.890
I LIKED KNOWING HE WAS THERE

28:00.890 --> 28:03.432
AND I WASN'T BY MYSELF.

28:03.432 --> 28:05.224
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

28:05.224 --> 28:07.686
[ SIGHS ]

28:09.438 --> 28:13.402
I CANNOT SLEEP WITH SOMEONE
LYING NEXT TO ME.

28:13.402 --> 28:15.274
LITERALLY CANNOT.

28:15.274 --> 28:18.027
MY ONE SERIOUS GUY? DEAN.

28:18.027 --> 28:21.410
DEAN JUST LOVED TO SPOON
AND SNUGGLE,

28:21.410 --> 28:24.824
AND I WOULD JUST...
LIE THERE,

28:24.824 --> 28:26.325
[ LAUGHS ]
STARING UP SILENTLY,

28:26.325 --> 28:28.788
COUNTING THE SECONDS
UNTIL HE WOULD FALL ASLEEP

28:28.788 --> 28:31.040
AND I COULD SNEAK OFF
TO SLEEP ON THE SOFA.

28:31.040 --> 28:32.211
AND THEN
I'D SNEAK BACK INTO BED

28:32.211 --> 28:34.293
BEFORE HE WOKE UP
IN THE MORNING.
[ GIGGLES ]

28:34.293 --> 28:37.216
YEAH, PEOPLE THINK THAT'S A CUTE
STORY. IT'S NOT A CUTE STORY.

28:37.216 --> 28:39.428
THAT SOFA WAS HARD AS A ROCK.
I WAS EXHAUSTED.

28:41.550 --> 28:43.012
DEAN IS A REALLY SWEET GUY.

28:43.012 --> 28:46.685
HE'S TALL AND KIND.

28:46.685 --> 28:48.227
CIVIL RIGHTS LAWYER.

28:48.227 --> 28:50.519
HE'S FUNNY.

28:50.519 --> 28:54.193
SO WHEN HE PROPOSED,
I EXPLAINED TO HIM

28:54.193 --> 28:55.484
ABOUT THE SLEEPING.

28:55.484 --> 28:56.816
I SAID, "YOU KNOW,

28:56.816 --> 29:00.159
MAYBE YOU COULD SLEEP IN A ROOM
DOWN THE HALL."

29:00.159 --> 29:01.991
I WANTED TO SLEEP ALONE.

29:03.572 --> 29:04.824
AND WHAT HAPPENED?

29:04.824 --> 29:06.165
WELL, HE IS NOW MARRIED

29:06.165 --> 29:08.707
TO SOMEONE WHO LOVES
TO SPOON AND SNUGGLE.

29:08.707 --> 29:10.249
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:10.249 --> 29:12.751
AND I SLEEP LIKE A BABY
EVERY NIGHT.

29:15.134 --> 29:18.047
I MIGHT BE TOO GOOD
AT BEING ALONE.

29:18.047 --> 29:20.219
[ SIGHS ]

29:20.219 --> 29:24.223
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:24.223 --> 29:26.976
♪ LET THE LIGHT BACK IN ♪

29:26.976 --> 29:30.519
MAYBE I COULD...[ SIGHS ]
PRINT A DEREK.

29:30.519 --> 29:31.851
[ WHIRRING CONTINUES ]

29:31.851 --> 29:34.193
JUST FOR SLEEPING.

29:34.193 --> 29:35.895
♪ OOH ♪

29:35.895 --> 29:39.819
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:39.819 --> 29:43.662
♪ LET THE LIGHT BACK IN ♪

29:43.662 --> 29:47.366
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:47.366 --> 29:51.170
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

29:51.170 --> 29:54.173
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

30:08.227 --> 30:09.849
HEY, MOVE YOUR BUTT.

30:13.983 --> 30:16.735
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:16.735 --> 30:19.028
HELLO AGAIN, CYCLOPS.

30:19.028 --> 30:21.240
Jo: IT IS CRAZY COOL AMAZING.

30:21.240 --> 30:22.531
IT COULD NOT BE
MORE AMAZING.

30:22.531 --> 30:24.243
OKAY, HIT ME. WHAT'S NEXT?

30:24.243 --> 30:26.906
I THINK WE CAN DIVIDE
THE DIAPHRAGM

30:26.906 --> 30:29.038
TO RESECT
THE PERICARDIAL COMPONENT

30:29.038 --> 30:30.499
OF THE TUMOR.

30:30.499 --> 30:31.911
Maggie: BUT CAREFULLY.

30:31.911 --> 30:33.913
WE'LL NEED TO DISSECT
2 TO 3 CENTIMETERS

30:33.913 --> 30:37.796
PROXIMAL TO THE I.V.C. FIRST
TO CONTROL FLOW.

30:37.796 --> 30:39.128
YEP, AND THEN WE CAN CLAMP

30:39.128 --> 30:42.221
AND CREATE
THE VENO-VENOUS BYPASS FLAP.

30:42.221 --> 30:44.633
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANNA DO
A STERNOTOMY?

30:44.633 --> 30:46.465
NOW YOU HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY?
WHERE WERE YOU YESTERDAY?

30:46.465 --> 30:48.267
YOU SHOULD'VE SHOWED ME THIS.
KAREV, WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

30:48.267 --> 30:50.019
WELL...[ SIGHS ] I WOULD DO
McGINN'S TECHNIQUE

30:50.019 --> 30:52.061
TO ACCESS THE CHEST
WITH LESS INVASIVENESS

30:52.061 --> 30:55.234
TO AVOID DIAPHRAGMATIC HERNIA
POSTRADIATION.

30:55.234 --> 30:56.605
[ SIGHS ]

30:56.605 --> 30:59.188
HE'S GOT A POINT.
BACK TO THE BEGINNING.

31:01.150 --> 31:04.153
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

31:04.153 --> 31:07.156
♪♪♪

31:17.416 --> 31:19.338
Meredith: OKAY, SO FEEL THIS
RIGHT HERE.

31:19.338 --> 31:20.709
OKAY, THAT'S...WHAT?

31:20.709 --> 31:23.382
LIKE, 5 CENTIMETERS
SUPERIOR TO THE RENAL VEIN?

31:23.382 --> 31:24.593
OKAY, BUT STOP.

31:24.593 --> 31:26.385
CLOSE YOUR EYES

31:26.385 --> 31:27.927
AND JUST FEEL.
OKAY.

31:27.927 --> 31:32.061
BECAUSE ALL WE HAVE TO GO ON
IS MUSCLE MEMORY.

31:32.061 --> 31:35.684
UM, IT'S...
2 FINGERBREADTHS

31:35.684 --> 31:38.067
FROM THE CONFLUENCE
OF THE HEPATIC VEINS.

31:38.067 --> 31:41.400
AND THEN WE ANASTOMOSE
THE BIFURCATED GRAFT.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.112
BAILEY?
YEAH.

31:43.112 --> 31:44.363
WRITE THAT UP.

31:44.363 --> 31:47.366
♪♪♪

31:54.333 --> 31:56.705
YOU'RE THEIR BOARD BITCH.

31:56.705 --> 31:58.167
YOU'RE JEALOUS, AREN'T YOU?
NO.

31:58.167 --> 31:59.378
A LITTLE.

31:59.378 --> 32:01.540
WILSON!
OH, YEAH. UH, ON IT.

32:01.540 --> 32:04.543
♪♪♪

32:07.716 --> 32:10.599
OKAY, MY FINGER IS IN
THE FORAMEN OF WINSLOW.

32:10.599 --> 32:12.221
BAILEY, CAN YOU FEEL ME?

32:12.221 --> 32:13.432
YEAH, I'M RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

32:13.432 --> 32:16.225
I CAN FEEL THE EDGE
OF THE LESSER OMENTUM.

32:16.225 --> 32:17.816
I THINK THAT GIVES ME
ENOUGH SPACE

32:17.816 --> 32:19.938
TO CONTROL
THE PORTA HEPATIS.

32:19.938 --> 32:21.150
MM-HMM.

32:21.150 --> 32:23.152
YES. YES. I CAN PALPATE
A GOOD WINDOW.

32:23.152 --> 32:25.614
GOOD. THAT WORKS.

32:25.614 --> 32:27.196
[ CELL PHONE CHIMES
AND VIBRATES ]

32:27.196 --> 32:28.988
NO.
ALL RIGHT, WHAT NEXT?

32:28.988 --> 32:30.159
THERE IS NO NEXT.

32:30.159 --> 32:31.410
THE WOUND-V.A.C.
HAS FRANK BLOOD.

32:31.410 --> 32:33.622
SHE'S BLEEDING. WE HAVE TO
GET HER UP TO THE O.R.

32:33.622 --> 32:35.874
YOU NEED
AN EXTRA SET OF HANDS?
YES. WILSON'S.

32:35.874 --> 32:38.167
TAKE THAT WHITE BOARD. BRING IT
UP WHERE EVERYONE CAN SEE IT.

32:38.167 --> 32:41.000
WE HAVEN'T EVEN GOTTEN TO THE
RETROPERITONEAL DISSECTION YET.

32:41.000 --> 32:44.383
WE WILL WHEN WE GET UP THERE.
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT AS WE GO.

32:46.385 --> 32:48.507
YOU ARE COMING WITH ME.

32:49.388 --> 32:52.641
I'M INTO THE RETROHEPATIC AREA.
MORE SUCTION.

32:52.641 --> 32:55.594
Jo: OKAY, THEN YOU'RE ON
TO STEP TWO.

32:55.594 --> 32:58.357
STEP TWO -- ACCESS
THE PERICARDIAL I.V.C.

32:58.357 --> 33:00.309
BAILEY, A LITTLE MORE
RETRACTION?

33:00.309 --> 33:02.191
OKAY, I'M AT THE PERICARDIUM.

33:02.191 --> 33:06.025
WELL, IT BRANCHES 2 CENTIMETERS
IN EITHER DIRECTION,

33:06.025 --> 33:06.985
SO YOU'RE CLOSE.

33:06.985 --> 33:08.197
DAMN IT.
ADHESIONS HERE, TOO.

33:08.197 --> 33:09.868
Meredith: THERE'S
TOO MUCH BLOOD. SUCTION!

33:09.868 --> 33:11.990
I NEED TO DO A PARTIAL RESECTION
OF THE LIVER,

33:11.990 --> 33:13.452
BUT I JUST CAN'T SEE TO DO IT.
[ SUCTION GURGLING ]

33:13.452 --> 33:16.245
SAME PROBLEM UP HERE. CAN I GET
SOME MORE SUCTION, PLEASE?

33:16.245 --> 33:18.827
SHOULD WE CONTROL
THE HEPATIC VEINS

33:18.827 --> 33:21.170
AND RESECT PART OF THE LIVER?
I'M TRYING.

33:21.170 --> 33:22.501
I THINK THAT'S THE ONLY WAY.

33:22.501 --> 33:25.464
BUT WITHOUT VISIBILITY,
I MIGHT HIT A MAJOR VESSEL.

33:25.464 --> 33:27.176
PIERCE?

33:27.176 --> 33:28.467
I CAN'T SEE THE FIELD.

33:28.467 --> 33:30.339
YEAH, I CAN'T SEE ANYTHING.

33:31.970 --> 33:33.892
CRAP. THEY'RE DROWNING.

33:33.892 --> 33:35.684
I'M NOT SURE THE MODEL'S
GONNA HELP THEM.

33:35.684 --> 33:37.936
IT'S NOT TELLING THEM ANY MORE
THAN THE SCANS DID.

33:37.936 --> 33:39.058
AND THEY STILL CAN'T
SEE ENOUGH TO --

33:39.058 --> 33:40.559
THE MODEL IS HOW THEY'LL SEE,

33:40.559 --> 33:42.901
WITHOUT ADHESIONS AND BLEEDING
IN THE WAY.

33:42.901 --> 33:45.444
HOW THE PIECES RELATE
TO HER ANATOMY.

33:45.444 --> 33:48.026
IT'S THE BIG PICTURE.

33:48.026 --> 33:50.199
OH, MY GOD.

33:50.199 --> 33:51.570
I GET IT.

33:53.822 --> 33:55.033
YOU'RE WELCOME.

34:01.960 --> 34:03.582
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

34:03.582 --> 34:04.963
HOW'S IT COMING?

34:04.963 --> 34:06.875
YOU KNOW, BY MILLIMETERS.

34:06.875 --> 34:09.218
YOUR NOTEBOOK-WIELDING MINIONS
GOT BORED

34:09.218 --> 34:11.009
AND DITCHED ME
FOR ANOTHER TUMOR.

34:11.009 --> 34:14.553
WELL, I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
NEED THIS.

34:14.553 --> 34:17.055
ARE YOU KEEPING TABS ON ME?

34:17.055 --> 34:18.056
IS THAT WHAT'S HAPPENING?

34:18.056 --> 34:20.229
NO. WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

34:20.229 --> 34:22.060
BECAUSE YOU MIGHT BE WORRIED
ABOUT ME,

34:22.060 --> 34:23.352
AND THAT I...
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

34:23.352 --> 34:25.734
HAVE DECIDED I CAN DO SOMETHING
THAT CANNOT BE DONE

34:25.734 --> 34:28.397
JUST SO THAT I CAN PROVE
THAT I AM OKAY

34:28.397 --> 34:30.609
AND THAT I DESERVE TO BE HERE.

34:30.609 --> 34:31.820
THAT I'M OVERREACHING.

34:31.820 --> 34:34.743
SHOULD I BE KEEPING TABS
ON YOU?

34:34.743 --> 34:36.325
[ SCOFFS ] I MEAN,

34:36.325 --> 34:38.407
YOU SAW THE LOOK ON THOSE
RESIDENTS' FACES YESTERDAY.

34:38.407 --> 34:40.459
THEY THINK THAT I AM
CERTIFIABLE.

34:40.459 --> 34:42.541
AND...[ LAUGHS ]
WHY SHOULDN'T THEY?

34:42.541 --> 34:44.583
WHY SHOULD I THINK
THAT I CAN DO THIS?

34:44.583 --> 34:47.206
WHY SHOULDN'T I THINK THAT
I'M GONNA KILL THIS WOMAN

34:47.206 --> 34:48.207
AND ALL THOSE LITTLE BABIES
WITH HER?

34:48.207 --> 34:49.338
YOU ARE NOT DOING THAT. NO.

34:49.338 --> 34:51.300
NOBODY THINKS
THAT THIS CAN WORK.

34:51.300 --> 34:52.671
NO ONE UNDERSTANDS IT.

34:54.052 --> 34:56.555
YOU WERE TALKING WAY OVER
THOSE RESIDENTS' HEADS.

34:56.555 --> 34:59.978
AND YOU THINK SO FAST
IT MADE MY EYES SPIN.

34:59.978 --> 35:02.060
BUT YOU HAVE A PLAN.

35:02.060 --> 35:05.184
AND JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE THE ONLY
ONE THAT CAN SEE THE ENDGAME

35:05.184 --> 35:07.896
DOESN'T MEAN
THAT YOU'RE WRONG.

35:07.896 --> 35:10.108
IT JUST MEANS IT'S LONELY.

35:10.108 --> 35:13.822
AND SCARY.

35:13.822 --> 35:17.075
YOU'D BE A FOOL
IF YOU WEREN'T SCARED.

35:19.698 --> 35:20.829
[ BLOWS AIR ]

35:20.829 --> 35:22.040
I'M-A LEAVE YOU BE.

35:22.040 --> 35:24.243
UGH. DON'T. THEN I'LL BE ALONE
WITH THIS THING.

35:24.243 --> 35:26.044
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

35:28.207 --> 35:30.879
WHAT YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT
YESTERDAY...

35:30.879 --> 35:33.051
THE WHOLE BIG, BEAUTIFUL BODY?

35:33.051 --> 35:35.133
UM, I THINK I GET IT.

35:35.133 --> 35:36.134
I THINK.

35:36.134 --> 35:38.347
SO YOU DO
THE FLUOROSCEIN FIRST.

35:38.347 --> 35:39.598
TELL ME WHY.

35:39.598 --> 35:42.060
SO YOU CAN KEEP AN EYE
ON THE PITUITARY STALK

35:42.060 --> 35:43.892
EVEN THOUGH
YOU'RE NOWHERE NEAR IT.

35:43.892 --> 35:45.143
BECAUSE?

35:45.143 --> 35:46.355
BECAUSE...

35:46.355 --> 35:50.729
YOU WANT TO APPRECIATE
THE WHOLE THING AT ONCE.

35:50.729 --> 35:52.691
RIGHT?
YES.

35:52.691 --> 35:54.273
THANK YOU.

35:54.273 --> 35:56.074
YOU CAN GO NOW.

36:00.199 --> 36:01.620
Steph: [ CHUCKLES ]

36:03.952 --> 36:06.415
Meredith: OH, THERE. GOT IT.
JUST LIGATED THE HEPATIC VEINS.

36:06.415 --> 36:07.786
WHAT'S NEXT?

36:07.786 --> 36:09.548
OKAY, YOU JUST CONTROLLED
THE LOWER END OF THE TUMOR,

36:09.548 --> 36:11.049
SO...
[ SUCTION GURGLING ]

36:11.049 --> 36:14.132
THAT'S AS FAR AS YOU GOT.
THAT'S THE LAST STEP.

36:14.132 --> 36:15.344
[ SIGHS ]

36:15.344 --> 36:17.596
OKAY, SO NEXT WE...

36:17.596 --> 36:20.969
DISSECT AROUND THE DIAPHRAGM.
FINISH MY DISSECTION
RETROPERITONEALLY.

36:20.969 --> 36:23.852
UH, THAT'S...
TWO WAYS TO GO.

36:23.852 --> 36:27.266
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
HER HEART CAN'T HANDLE
ALL THE CLAMPING.

36:27.266 --> 36:28.767
WHATEVER WE DO,
WE HAVE TO DO IT NOW.

36:28.767 --> 36:30.018
YOU MEAN CUT BLIND?

36:31.360 --> 36:34.943
NO. WAIT. JO, BRING THE CYCLOPS
OVER HERE.

36:34.943 --> 36:35.984
ON IT.
BRING IT OVER HERE,

36:35.984 --> 36:37.986
HOLD IT UP, TURN IT SLOWLY.

36:39.818 --> 36:44.122
OKAY, SO WE'RE GONNA ANASTOMOSE
THE GRAFT TO THE LOWER END.

36:44.122 --> 36:45.914
AND THEN I'LL START
FROM THE UPPER END, YEAH.

36:45.914 --> 36:47.536
OKAY.

36:47.536 --> 36:48.917
FIND ME.

36:48.917 --> 36:50.289
I AM AT THE DIAPHRAGM.

36:50.289 --> 36:52.631
6-OH PROLENE AND GRAFT STAT.

36:52.631 --> 36:55.254
I'M ON TOP OF
THE RIGHT HEPATIC VEIN.

36:55.254 --> 36:57.215
THIS IS WHERE WE CUT,
RIGHT HERE.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.047
THAT'S MY FINGER.

36:59.047 --> 37:01.099
OH. OKAY.

37:01.099 --> 37:02.891
NO, IT'S, UH...

37:02.891 --> 37:05.394
GOT IT. HERE. IT EXTENDS
10cm OFF WHERE THE VEINS MEET.

37:05.394 --> 37:08.186
RIGHT? THIS IS IT.
THIS IS IT RIGHT HERE.

37:08.186 --> 37:09.478
THIS IS WHERE WE CUT RIGHT HERE.

37:10.939 --> 37:12.691
HOW MUCH DO YOU TRUST
THAT THING?

37:12.691 --> 37:15.984
I'LL LET YOU KNOW IN A SECOND.
METZ.

37:15.984 --> 37:17.856
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

37:17.856 --> 37:21.860
[ MONITOR CONTINUES
BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

37:28.827 --> 37:30.369
NO EXCESS BLEEDING.

37:30.369 --> 37:31.870
NOT ANY MORE THAN BEFORE.

37:31.870 --> 37:33.712
YOUR DISSECTION
WAS FLAWLESS.

37:33.712 --> 37:35.213
THEN SHE'S COMIN' OUT.

37:35.213 --> 37:39.798
OKAY, CYCLOPS,
SHOW ME THAT UGLY FACE.

37:39.798 --> 37:42.801
[ SQUISHING ]

37:42.801 --> 37:47.596
UGH! SO GROSS
AND SO FREAKING COOL! [ LAUGHS ]

37:47.596 --> 37:49.097
OH! GOT SOME BLEEDERS!

37:49.097 --> 37:52.521
BEAUTIFUL BLEEDERS,
RIGHT WHERE WE CAN SEE THEM.

37:52.521 --> 37:55.063
Jetta: ♪ RUNNING THROUGH
THE BLACK NIGHT ♪

37:55.063 --> 37:58.236
♪ I'M SURE
I HAD THE GREEN LIGHT ♪

37:58.236 --> 38:01.069
♪ CAR RAN OVER ♪

38:01.069 --> 38:03.862
♪ I THOUGHT THAT I WOULD DIE ♪

38:03.862 --> 38:06.405
♪ THEN FROM THE X-RAY ♪

38:06.405 --> 38:08.497
♪ BACK TO THE RAT RACE ♪

38:08.497 --> 38:10.118
OH! [ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

38:10.118 --> 38:14.333
SHE WAS...
REALLY PRETTY.

38:14.333 --> 38:17.175
THE...WOMAN.

38:17.175 --> 38:18.176
AT THE BAR.
OH.

38:18.176 --> 38:22.050
WITH THE NICE TRANSDUCERS.

38:22.050 --> 38:24.092
UGH. I'M NOT READY.

38:24.092 --> 38:26.054
YOU GOTTA START SOMETIME.

38:26.054 --> 38:27.516
OWEN...[ CHUCKLES ]

38:27.516 --> 38:29.017
THE LAST WOMAN THAT I KISSED
IN THAT BAR,

38:29.017 --> 38:30.228
I ENDED UP MARRYING.

38:30.228 --> 38:32.641
WELL, MAYBE JUST
TAKE THE NEXT ONE HOME THEN.

38:32.641 --> 38:33.892
UH...
RIGHT?

38:33.892 --> 38:35.734
SHUT UP.
[ LAUGHS ]

38:35.734 --> 38:37.776
HEY, YOU'RE NOT READY EITHER.

38:37.776 --> 38:39.027
YOU KNOW,
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE IT.

38:39.027 --> 38:41.360
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ] MM.
IT'S SEX.

38:41.360 --> 38:44.032
SURE, YOU KNOW, I'VE GONE OUT
AND HAD ONE-NIGHT STANDS BEFORE.

38:44.032 --> 38:46.575
MM-HMM.
BUT...

38:46.575 --> 38:48.497
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
I DON'T KNOW.

38:48.497 --> 38:51.289
I CAN'T...

38:51.289 --> 38:54.543
SOMETHING REAL?

38:54.543 --> 38:56.835
I PULLED THAT ICICLE
OUT OF HER CHEST.

38:56.835 --> 39:01.169
HELL, I-I BATHED HER WHEN
SHE COULDN'T BATHE HERSELF.

39:01.169 --> 39:04.132
I CAN'T IMAGINE BELONGING
TO ANYONE LIKE THAT AGAIN.

39:06.094 --> 39:09.057
HAVE WE USED UP
ALL OUR HAPPY?

39:09.057 --> 39:10.268
♪ I PAY A HIGH PRICE ♪

39:10.268 --> 39:13.562
YOU EVER AFRAID OF THAT,
THAT THIS IS ALL THERE IS NOW?

39:13.562 --> 39:15.063
IT'S LIKE I HAD
A CERTAIN AMOUNT OF HAPPY

39:15.063 --> 39:16.274
THAT WAS SUPPOSED TO LAST
MY WHOLE LIFE,

39:16.274 --> 39:17.896
AND I'VE USED IT ALL UP.

39:19.187 --> 39:20.399
DO YOU THINK THAT'S TRUE?

39:22.150 --> 39:23.942
GOD, I HOPE NOT.
HUH.

39:23.942 --> 39:25.654
Meredith: THE LAST TRUE HERMIT
WAS FOUND

39:25.654 --> 39:29.488
AND DRAGGED OUT OF HIDING
AND INTO THE WORLD.

39:29.488 --> 39:31.620
MOST MIGHT FIND
HIS EXISTENCE SAD,

39:31.620 --> 39:32.991
BUT THE HERMIT KNEW
SOMETHING WE DIDN'T.

39:32.991 --> 39:34.793
[ RINGTONE PLAYS ]

39:34.793 --> 39:36.044
MM! PAUSE!

39:36.044 --> 39:38.837
NO!
[ GRUNTS ]

39:38.837 --> 39:41.840
OH! STEPH'S ROCKING NEURO
WITH GIRL SHEPHERD.

39:41.840 --> 39:44.883
SHE GOT ASSIGNED
HER CRAZY TUMOR! YEAH!

39:44.883 --> 39:46.214
WHO TAUGHT YOU "PAUSE"?

39:46.214 --> 39:48.767
OH, UM, GREY TOLD ME ABOUT IT
WHEN WE WERE SCRUBBING OUT.

39:48.767 --> 39:51.720
GREAT RULE. NOW...

39:51.720 --> 39:54.062
UNPAUSE.

39:54.062 --> 39:55.684
[ GRUNTS ]

39:55.684 --> 39:57.646
♪ TIME, IT FINALLY FEELS ♪

39:57.646 --> 40:02.150
HE KNEW THAT WHEN
IT COMES DOWN TO IT,

40:02.150 --> 40:03.732
EVEN WHEN
YOU'RE WITH SOMEONE...

40:03.732 --> 40:06.735
[ FAN BLADES WHIRRING ]

40:06.735 --> 40:08.657
♪ OH, WHOA ♪

40:08.657 --> 40:11.740
♪ OH, WHOA, OH ♪

40:11.740 --> 40:13.742
♪ OH, WHOA ♪

40:13.742 --> 40:18.537
OR IN THE NOISY RUSH
OF PEOPLE...
[ AIR WHOOSHING ]

40:18.537 --> 40:21.960
♪ OH, WHOA, OH ♪

40:29.177 --> 40:32.601
[ AIR TURNS OFF,
BLADES CONTINUE WHIRRING ]

40:32.601 --> 40:34.012
IT'S JUST YOU.

40:34.012 --> 40:38.767
♪ UNDER THE MOTEL NEON SIGN ♪

40:38.767 --> 40:40.148
♪ ROOM 105 ♪

40:40.148 --> 40:41.770
THE ONE YOU CAN COUNT ON...

40:41.770 --> 40:43.732
♪ THE BACK OF THE ALLEY ♪

40:43.732 --> 40:45.113
AND LEAN ON...

40:45.113 --> 40:46.655
♪ YOU'RE WEARING MY COAT ♪

40:46.655 --> 40:47.986
AND DEPEND ON.

40:47.986 --> 40:50.238
[ BEEP, DIALING ]

40:50.238 --> 40:51.449
IT HAS TO BE YOU.

40:51.449 --> 40:53.411
Hi.
HEY.

40:53.411 --> 40:55.954
Is something wrong?

40:55.954 --> 40:56.955
NO.

40:56.955 --> 40:58.787
JUST...WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

40:58.787 --> 41:00.999
Nothing.

41:00.999 --> 41:03.041
Nothing. You?

41:03.041 --> 41:05.964
I'M JUST LYING IN BED
WITH MY TUMOR.

41:05.964 --> 41:08.466
Aw! You brought it home.
[ LAUGHS ]

41:08.466 --> 41:10.088
Can I see it?
MM-HMM.

41:10.088 --> 41:11.299
AND ONCE YOU FIGURE THAT OUT...

41:11.299 --> 41:12.511
[ Gasps ]

41:12.511 --> 41:13.592
THAT'S WHEN BEING ALONE...

41:13.592 --> 41:16.054
Well...

41:16.054 --> 41:18.977
it's no 3-D husband,
but it's something.

41:18.977 --> 41:20.058
IT'LL DO FOR NOW.

41:20.058 --> 41:22.100
[ Laughs ] Oh, my god.
I have to...

41:22.100 --> 41:23.401
BECOMES A CHOICE.

41:23.401 --> 41:27.736
♪ LIKE COMING HOME ♪

41:27.736 --> 41:30.488
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

41:30.488 --> 41:34.282
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

41:35.784 --> 41:37.455
[ DOOR OPENS ]

41:38.376 --> 41:40.168
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:41.329 --> 41:43.381
UM, IT'LL BE A MINUTE.

41:49.337 --> 41:53.011
[ Whispers ] OKAY.

41:53.011 --> 41:54.222
WHAT?

41:54.222 --> 41:57.806
THIS IS A BIG GUNS CONVERSATION,
ISN'T IT?

42:00.348 --> 42:01.690
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

42:01.690 --> 42:02.901
YEAH.

42:04.943 --> 42:06.144
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

42:06.144 --> 42:08.526
APRIL, JACKSON,

42:08.526 --> 42:10.108
WE HAVE YOUR TEST RESULTS.
